Ann Winterton: Obviously, if someone had capacity, there would be the ability to ask them whether they consented to such a test. The consent rule would still apply there. There is, in a sense, a slight difference here;
14 Dec 2004 : Column 1600
if someone cannot give consent because they are incapacitated, there have to be other ways in which the approach could be made.

